"title": "5185: stomach",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5185: stomach",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>As well as the physical stomach, the term is used in association with God's judgment or in a figurative sense.</p>\n<h2>Stomach as part of the physical body</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:13\">1CO 6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:16\">JOB 40:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:2\">SNG 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:32\">DAN 2:32</a></p>\n<h3>Jonah in the stomach of a huge fish</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:40\">MAT 12:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:17-Jonah2:1\">JON 1:17–2:1</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual laws concerning the stomach</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:18-Mark7:19\">MRK 7:18–7:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:17\">MAT 15:17</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:41-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:41–11:45</a></p>\n<h2>Afflictions of the stomach</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:16\">LUK 15:16</a> <em>hunger</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:23\">1TI 5:23</a> <em>illness</em></p>\n<h2>Fatal wounding in the stomach</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:21\">JDG 3:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:23\">2SA 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:27\">2SA 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:6\">2SA 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:10\">2SA 20:10</a></p>\n<h2>The stomach and God's judgment</h2>\n<h3>Severe stomach pain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:6-Jer30:7\">JER 30:6–30:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:20-Num5:22\">NUM 5:20–5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:27\">NUM 5:27</a></p>\n<h3>Crawling on one's stomach as a sign of submission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:14\">GEN 3:14</a></strong> <em>Part of God's curse upon Satan.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:9\">PSA 72:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:23\">ISA 49:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:25\">ISA 65:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:17\">MIC 7:17</a></p>\n<h3>Hunger as a result of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:14\">MIC 6:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:12-Job20:15\">JOB 20:12–20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:20-Job20:23\">JOB 20:20–20:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:25\">PRO 13:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:20\">ISA 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:19\">EZK 7:19</a></p>\n<h3>An empty stomach as a warning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:6\">AMO 4:6</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The stomach and God's blessing</h2>\n<p>In the OT a full stomach was one sign of God's blessing:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:9-Ps34:10\">PSA 34:9–34:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:19\">PSA 37:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:25\">PSA 37:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:3\">PRO 10:3</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative uses of the stomach</h2>\n<h3>Stomach as a symbol of inner thoughts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:3\">EZK 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:8\">PRO 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:22\">PRO 26:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:9-Rev10:10\">REV 10:9–10:10</a></p>\n<h3>Stomach as a symbol of worldliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:19\">PHP 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:18\">ROM 16:18</a></p>\n<h3>Stomach as something to be filled</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:20\">PRO 18:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:2\">JOB 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:34\">JER 51:34</a></p>",
